\description{
Builds the \code{targets} pipeline steps for a high-dimensional WGCNA (hdWGCNA)
co-expression network analysis, following the hdWGCNA basic + differential
module-eigengene tutorials. A single shared metacell-preparation step
(\code{wgcna_prep}) is created once, and the per-group steps below are created for
every element of \code{group} (target names carry the group, e.g. \code{wgcna_mait}):
}
\details{
\itemize{
\item \code{wgcna_prep} — RNA assay prep (join layers, normalise, variable features,
scale) then \code{SetupForWGCNA} + \code{MetacellsByGroups} and the metacell embedding.
\item \verb{wgcna_<group>_powertest} — \code{SetDatExpr} for the group + \code{TestSoftPowers}.
\item \verb{wgcna_<group>_soft_power} — the soft power chosen exactly as
\code{hdWGCNA::PlotSoftPowers} highlights it (lowest tested power with
\code{SFT.R.sq >= sft_rsquared}).
\item \verb{wgcna_<group>} — \code{ConstructNetwork} (at the selected soft power) +
\code{ModuleEigengenes} + \code{ModuleConnectivity} + \code{ResetModuleNames}, and, when
\code{trait_col} is given, \code{ModuleTraitCorrelation} of the modules against one-hot
indicators of each \code{trait_groups} level. The correlation is computed once
across all of the group's cells (a single constant \code{group.by}), so the stored
result has only an \code{"all_cells"} entry and is not split by the object's
cluster identities.
\item \verb{wgcna_<group>_dmes} — differential module eigengenes (\code{FindDMEs}) for every
pairwise comparison of \code{trait_groups} within the group (only created when
\code{trait_col} and \code{trait_groups} are supplied).
\item \verb{wgcna_<group>_enrichr} — module gene-set enrichment via \code{RunEnrichr}, run
once per \code{enrichr_dbs} entry and row-bound into a single data frame (each row
tagged with its \code{db}); created when \code{run_enrichr = TRUE}.
}

All values passed to the hdWGCNA / WGCNA functions are exposed as arguments.
Every step that uses WGCNA multithreading or loads the whole shared Seurat
object is \strong{pinned to \code{main}} and is \emph{not} affected by \code{deployment} /
\code{controller}: \code{wgcna_prep}, the power test, the soft-power pick, the network
and the Enrichr step. WGCNA's threading is incompatible with \code{crew} workers,
and the power test / network hold a full copy of the object. Only the
differential-module-eigengene step (\verb{wgcna_<group>_dmes}, a Wilcoxon test)
honours \code{deployment} and \code{controller}, so it can be sent to a worker (and to a
named controller when a controller group is used). \code{tom_name} is set to the
group label.
}
